# Recursion Tree / DP Table / Diagram

There is **no recursion** and **no DP** in this problem.

Mathematical representation:

```text
Length = k

x
│
├── x
├── x+1
├── x+2
├── ...
└── x+k-1

Sum

kx + k(k−1)/2 = n
```

---

# Why This Works

For every possible sequence length,

```text
n = kx + k(k−1)/2
```

If

```text
x = (n - k(k−1)/2)/k
```

is

* an integer
* positive

then those consecutive numbers uniquely form one valid sequence.

Since every valid sequence has exactly one length `k` and one starting value `x`, checking all feasible lengths counts every representation exactly once.

